        <updateDate>2021-07-28T16:34:11Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Fully Informed Veteran Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs to authorize physicians and other health care providers of the Veterans Health Administration to provide veterans with information about participating in state-approved marijuana programs if their state has such a program available. Under the bill, the term <em>state</em> includes the District of Columbia, federally recognized tribes, and U.S. territories and possessions. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
